f with great injustices and none forgives sin but You, so forgive me and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":953,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/08\/01\/qiyam-al-layl-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":2780,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Forgiveness for night prayer in Ramadan","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 1, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, encouraged standing for night prayer in the month of Ramadan, without imposing it on them. The Prophet would say, \u201cWhoever stands in prayer during Ramadan due to faith and seeking reward, his previous sins will be forgiven.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":863,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/06\/12\/best-to-avoid-hudud-punishments\/","url_meta":{"origin":2780,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Hudud: Best to avoid legal punishments if possible","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 12, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: A man came to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, I have committed an offense, so impose punishment upon me.\u201d The man was present at the prayer and he prayed with the Prophet. When they\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_contex